The following code prints `488447264` on the playpen, which is bad: (http://is.gd/k4cPWw)

``` rust
fn main() {
    let mut a;
    a += { a = 2; 3 };
    println!("{:?}", a);
}
```

IMO `+=` should be simply a sugar for

``` rust
AddAssign::add_assign(&mut self, rhs);
```

where AddAssign is some trait [added in the future](https://github.com/rust-lang/rfcs/issues/393) to overload `+=`.

``` rust
a = 0;
AddAssign::add_assign(&mut a, &{ a = 22; 2 });
```

